# Laura's ZSH Quick-Help

**FZF key-bindings**  
Ctrl-t   – Fuzzy-find files and insert their path  
Alt-c    – Fuzzy-cd (jump into a selected directory)  
Ctrl-r   – Fuzzy-search command history  
Alt-d    – Fuzzy-cd including hidden dirs (custom wrapper)

**Every-day aliases**  
..            → cd ..  
:q            → clear  
bat           → acpi -a -b -t                 # Battery + temp  
cls           → clear                         # Muscle-memory from Windows  
v             → nvim                          # Open NeoVim  
zshrc         → nvim ~/.zshrc && source ~/.zshrc  

**Package helpers**  
upgrate       → sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade  
aptdeps       → sudo apt-get install -f  
aptfix        → sudo apt --fix-broken install  

**Git shortcuts**  
lg            → git log --graph --oneline --decorate  
gd            → git diff --color | diff-so-fancy  
pull          → git pull  

**Networking**  
myip          → curl ipinfo.io/ip  
ports         → netstat -tulanp  
nmapQuick     → nmap -F  
trace         → traceroute  

**Fun & misc**  
dad           – Get a random dad joke  
speed         – speedtest-cli  
firmware      – systemctl reboot --firmware-setup  

**Custom functions**  
fzf_cd_hidden – Implementation behind Alt-d (see ~/.zshrc)  
sendip        – Post your public IP to your webhook
